ull,\"attribution\":0.04198473282442748,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":1354,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.03816793893129771,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":59391,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.03435114503816794,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":2595704,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.022900763358778622,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":2054658,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.022900763358778622,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":89795,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.022900763358778622,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":400160,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.022900763358778622,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":1490398,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.022900763358778622,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":8357,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.011450381679389311,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":1172378,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.0076335877862595426,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":8056396,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.0076335877862595426,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":3915568,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.0038167938931297713,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"acceptedBy\":7,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"iqByAction\":{},\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null,\"pyong\":false,\"cosign\":false},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"cosign\",\"uncosign\",\"destroy\",\"accept\",\"reject\",\"see_unreviewed\",\"clear_votes\",\"propose_edit_to\",\"pin_to_profile\",\"unpin_from_profile\",\"update_source\",\"edit_custom_preview\",\"create_comment\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":1065,\"verified\":false,\"url\":\"https://genius.com/3490523/Eminem-stan/Stan\",\"twitterShareMessage\":\"â€œIn this song, Eminem corresponds with a crazed fan who becomes increasingly unhinged as the story progreâ€¦â€ â€”@Genius\",\"state\":\"accepted\",\"source\":null,\"shareUrl\":\"https://genius.com/3490523\",\"referentId\":3490523,\"pyongsCount\":7,\"proposedEditCount\":0,\"pinned\":false,\"needsExegesis\":false,\"id\":3490523,\"hasVoters\":true,\"embedContent\":\"<blockquote class=\'rg_standalone_container\' data-src=\'//genius.com/annotations/3490523/standalone_embed\'><a href=\'https://genius.com/3490523/Eminem-stan/Stan\'>Stan<\/a><br><a href=\'https://genius.com/Eminem-stan-lyrics\'>&#8213; Eminem (Ft.Â Dido) â€“ Stan<\/a><\/blockquote><script async crossorigin src=\'//genius.com/annotations/load_standalone_embeds.js\'><\/script>\",\"deleted\":false,\"customPreview\":null,\"createdAt\":1279572491,\"community\":true,\"commentCount\":6,\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"In this song, Eminem corresponds with a crazed fan who becomes increasingly unhinged as the story progresses. This is one of his most well-received singles and was listed at #15 on [VH1](http://www.vh1.com)\'s [Top 100 Hip Hop Songs of All Time](http://ifelicious.com/2008/09/25/vh-1s-list-of-top-100-hip-hop-songs-of-all-time/).\\n\\nEminem intended for this song to be [a message to fans](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c2R6yvdKPqA) who had written him disturbing letters indicating that they had taken [*The Slim Shady LP*](https://genius.com/albums/Eminem/The-slim-shady-lp-expanded-edition)\'s violent lyrics seriously. Another reason Em wrote this was to [\\\"make the critics who were saying things about [him] feel stupid.\\\"](https://youtu.be/AwLQxWiOTEI) His aim was to disprove those who felt he lacked talent and relied on shock value.\\n\\nThis song has cemented itself in history, with \\\"Stan\\\" being entered into the [Oxford Dictionary](http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/stan) as an informal noun. It is generally considered to be a portmanteau of \\\"stalker\\\" and \\\"fan,\\\" but Oxford defines the term as:\\n\\n>An overzealous or obsessive fan of a particular celebrity.\\n\\nIn a 2011 [Shade 45](https://m.siriusxm.com/shade45) appearance, Em [revealed that](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p_x0KBndWDI):\\n\\n> There was a verse where [Stan] got out of the water. He escaped and came to my house to kill me. Then I had to kill him first, [but] I missed him, and he was in the hospital for like three weeks. Then he was pissed off that I didn\'t write him get-well cards, so he came to kill me again, and in the last verse finally I just blew his head off.\\n\\nIn 2013, Eminem released a follow-up in the form of [\\\"Bad Guy,\\\"](http://genius.com/Eminem-bad-guy-lyrics) wherein Stan\'s younger brother Matthew avenges his brother\'s death.\",\"html\":\"<p>In this song, Eminem corresponds with a crazed fan who becomes increasingly unhinged as the story progresses. This is one of his most well-received singles and was listed at #15 on <a href=\\\"http://www.vh1.com/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">VH1<\/a>â€™s <a href=\\\"http://ifelicious.com/2008/09/25/vh-1s-list-of-top-100-hip-hop-songs-of-all-time/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">Top 100 Hip Hop Songs of All Time<\/a>.<\/p>\\n\\n<p>Eminem intended for this song to be <a href=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c2R6yvdKPqA\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">a message to fans<\/a> who had written him disturbing letters indicating that they had taken <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/albums/Eminem/The-slim-shady-lp-expanded-edition\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/albums/506752\\\"><em>The Slim Shady LP<\/em><\/a>â€™s violent lyrics seriously. Another reason Em wrote this was to <a href=\\\"https://youtu.be/AwLQxWiOTEI\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">â€œmake the critics who were saying things about [him] feel stupid.â€<\/a> His aim was to disprove those who felt he lacked talent and relied on shock value.<\/p>\\n\\n<p>This song has cemented itself in history, with â€œStanâ€ being entered into the <a href=\\\"http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/stan\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">Oxford Dictionary<\/a> as an informal noun. It is generally considered to be a portmanteau of â€œstalkerâ€ and â€œfan,â€ but Oxford defines the term as:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockquote><p>An overzealous or obsessive fan of a particular celebrity.<\/p><\/blockquote>\\n\\n<p>In a 2011 <a href=\\\"https://m.siriusxm.com/shade45\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">Shade 45<\/a> appearance, Em <a href=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p_x0KBndWDI\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">revealed that<\/a>:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockquote><p>There was a verse where [Stan] got out of the water. He escaped and came to my house to kill me. Then I had to kill him first, [but] I missed him, and he was in the hospital for like three weeks. Then he was pissed off that I didnâ€™t write him get-well cards, so he came to kill me again, and in the last verse finally I just blew his head off.<\/p><\/blockquote>\\n\\n<p>In 2013, Eminem released a follow-up in the form of <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/Eminem-bad-guy-lyrics\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/songs/235723\\\">â€œBad Guy,â€<\/a> wherein Stanâ€™s younger brother Matthew avenges his brotherâ€™s death.<\/p>\"},\"beingCreated\":false,\"apiPath\":\"/annotations/3490523\",\"type\":\"annotation\"}},\"referents\":{\"24878\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":24878},\"24879\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":24879},\"24880\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":24880},\"24883\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":24883},\"24886\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":24886},\"26018\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":26018},\"26270\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":26270},\"26272\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":26272},\"26287\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":26287},\"26303\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\"