Role\":null,\"attribution\":0.05063291139240507,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":251069,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.012658227848101267,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":36,\"id\":14473,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1481891563,\"bodyForEdit\":\"Yes, being \\\"Stan\\\" one of his greatest successes, he performed it several times. He did it [with Dido](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xLCmIhKH2Ik), and also [with Elton John](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fm4IMpbTFrk).\\nThe live version with Elton John has been included in  *Curtain Call: The Hits* album, in 2005. It was a quite controversial performance, because Eminem was accused of being an homophobe due to his lyrics, and Elton John is openly gay, but everything turned out great between the artists, who became close friends along the years.\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"Yes, being \\\"Stan\\\" one of his greatest successes, he performed it several times. He did it [with Dido](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xLCmIhKH2Ik), and also [with Elton John](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fm4IMpbTFrk).\\nThe live version with Elton John has been included in  *Curtain Call: The Hits* album, in 2005. It was a quite controversial performance, because Eminem was accused of being an homophobe due to his lyrics, and Elton John is openly gay, but everything turned out great between the artists, who became close friends along the years.\",\"html\":\"<p>Yes, being â€œStanâ€ one of his greatest successes, he performed it several times. He did it <a href=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xLCmIhKH2Ik\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">with Dido<\/a>, and also <a href=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fm4IMpbTFrk\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">with Elton John<\/a>.<br>\\nThe live version with Elton John has been included in  <em>Curtain Call: The Hits<\/em> album, in 2005. It was a quite controversial performance, because Eminem was accused of being an homophobe due to his lyrics, and Elton John is openly gay, but everything turned out great between the artists, who became close friends along the years.<\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"19915\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":3403363,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":70,\"id\":19915,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1485178567,\"bodyForEdit\":\"In a televised interview from 2000, Eminem explains:\\n\\n\\\"Basically it\'s just about crazy fan mail that I get from people, and it\'s about a kid who is really sick, you know what I\'m saying? He takes everything I say literally like if I say I wanna slit my wrists then he wants to slit his wrists. He\'s crazy for real, like I\'m not, and it\'s like everything I say he can relate to. So at the end of the song, he ends up committing suicide and driving his girlfriend off a cliff and it\'s really crazy. But it\'s kind of like a message to the fans to let them know that everything I say is not meant to be taken literally. Just most of the things\\\".\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"In a televised interview from 2000, Eminem explains:\\n\\n\\\"Basically it\'s just about crazy fan mail that I get from people, and it\'s about a kid who is really sick, you know what I\'m saying? He takes everything I say literally like if I say I wanna slit my wrists then he wants to slit his wrists. He\'s crazy for real, like I\'m not, and it\'s like everything I say he can relate to. So at the end of the song, he ends up committing suicide and driving his girlfriend off a cliff and it\'s really crazy. But it\'s kind of like a message to the fans to let them know that everything I say is not meant to be taken literally. Just most of the things\\\".\",\"html\":\"<p>In a televised interview from 2000, Eminem explains:<\/p>\\n\\n<p>â€œBasically itâ€™s just about crazy fan mail that I get from people, and itâ€™s about a kid who is really sick, you know what Iâ€™m saying? He takes everything I say literally like if I say I wanna slit my wrists then he wants to slit his wrists. Heâ€™s crazy for real, like Iâ€™m not, and itâ€™s like everything I say he can relate to. So at the end of the song, he ends up committing suicide and driving his girlfriend off a cliff and itâ€™s really crazy. But itâ€™s kind of like a message to the fans to let them know that everything I say is not meant to be taken literally. Just most of the thingsâ€.<\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"38062\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":1434108,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":6,\"id\":38062,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1496381485,\"bodyForEdit\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RoCeArB2ctM\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RoCeArB2ctM\",\"html\":\"<p><\/p><div class=\\\"embedly_preview embedly_preview--video\\\">\\n<iframe loading=\\\"lazy\\\" type=\\\"text/html\\\" width=\\\"640\\\" height=\\\"390\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen=\\\"1\\\" src=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/RoCeArB2ctM?modestbranding=1&amp;start=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=genius.com\\\"><\/iframe>\\n<\/div>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"108393\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":5754203,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":59,\"id\":108393,\"hasVoters\":t